review.body:
Thanks for your work and this contribution! Beyond the single comments, one general question: Why is there a need for inclusion of key and certificate material? Could this be eliminated? From a security (and code-scanning) perspective this is not really advisable. Isn't the availability of the "gen_cert.sh" script sufficient? 

Finally, is the understanding correct that you don't want the resultant image(s) to be hosted in the "openquantumsafe" namespace at docker hub? If so, this PR doesn't really need the separate USAGE.md file (as that is what we push to docker hub when publishing an image into "openquantumsafe", i.e., won't need that when not publishing it there). If in turn it would be a goal to publish the image to "openquantumsafe/envoy", there should be a CI script entry added building, testing and pushing the image (see https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/oqs-demos/blob/main/.circleci/config.yml for examples). Lastly, please consider adding a line entry to the main oqs-demos README with your name and the relevant links (see other projects/contributor entries for examples). Thanks again!
